    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-25T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-25T11:30:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">330/6–2550: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-25T22:00:00+05:30"
                            >June 25, 1950—10 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 25—3:39 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>928. I telephoned Bajpai who is in charge <gloss target="#t_MEA1">MEA</gloss>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d79fn1">Girja S. Bajpai was Secretary General of the Indian
                        Ministry of External Affairs.</note> at 9 p. m., immediately on receipt
                        <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss> June 25<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d79fn2">See footnote 1 to telegram 613, June 25, 2 a. m., to Seoul,
                            <ref target="#pg_128">p. 128</ref>.</note> in order inform him its
                    contents.</p>
                <p>He stated impossible get into communication <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>
                    representative to SC this evening but he was confident B. N. Rau in framework of
                    standing instructions and as President of SC would do all proper in matter of
                    presiding over Council.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> could not issue any instructions of
                    substantive character until it had more complete information of what was going
                    on in Korea.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
